genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: AFGHANISTAN
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Islamic Republic of Afghanistan" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Islamic Republic of Afghanistan". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'fa'/'fas' as "Afghānistān" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Afghānestān".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: AKROTIRI
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard includes these ISO user-assigned code elements for Akrotiri. A numeric code element has additionally been assigned by the CCWG.
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Akrotiri is part of a British Overseas Territory and under British sovereignty. It is not clear whether ISO 3166/MA considers the code elements for the entry named "UNITED KINGDOM" as covering the territories of Akrotiri and Dhekelia; however, neither Akrotiri nor Dhekelia appears in the ISO 3166-2 administrative subdivisions of the United Kingdom, so the presumption is that their territory is not included under that entry (see ISO 3166-2:2013, Clause 4.1.2 (on subdivision)). The two Sovereign Base Areas of Akrotiri and Dhekelia together constitute the British Overseas Territory on Cyprus that was ceded to the United Kingdom in the 1960 Treaty of Establishment, in which the U.K. granted independence to the Crown Colony of Cyprus; the U.K., Cyprus, and Turkey were all signatories to that treaty. Note that British Overseas Territories are not considered part of the territory of the United Kingdom (see [http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-us/what-we-do/overseas-territories].) Apart from the Sovereign Base Areas on Cyprus, all of the other British Overseas Territories have their own separate entries in ISO 3166-1 (and in the GENC Standard as well).

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: ALBANIA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Albania" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Albania". The GENC Standard does not include the local short name "Shqipëri" in 'sq'/'sqi'.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: ALGERIA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "People’s Democratic Republic of Algeria" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the People's Democratic Republic of Algeria". Note that ISO 3166-1 consistently uses the incorrect character U+0027 rather than U+2019.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: AMERICAN SAMOA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Territory of American Samoa" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "American Samoa". Additionally, in order to correct a naming anomaly the GENC Standard specifies the remarks "Principal island: Tutuila; Includes Swains Island." while ISO 3166-1 specifies "Principal island: Tutuila; Includes Swain's Island."
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because GENC Standard considers the geographic territory of American Samoa to be specifically excluded from the geographic territory of the entry named "UNITED STATES". Note that the ISO 3166/MA considers the United States as including the geographic territory of American Samoa; while ISO 3166-1 includes an entry named "AMERICAN SAMOA", ISO 3166-2 specifies a code element for American Samoa as a corresponding administrative subdivision (of type "outlying area") of the entry named "UNITED STATES" (see ISO 3166-1:2013, Clause 4.3 "Overlaps"; and ISO 3166-2:2013, Clause 4.1.2 (on subdivision)).

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Principality of Andorra" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Principality of Andorra".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Angola" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Angola".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: ANGUILLA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Anguilla is a British Overseas Territory. British Overseas Territories are distinct areas that are not part of the territory of the United Kingdom. There are 14 such territories, including: Anguilla; Bermuda; British Antarctic Territory; British Indian Ocean Territory; British Virgin Islands; Cayman Islands; Falkland Islands (Islas Malvinas); Gibraltar; Montserrat; Pitcairn Islands; Saint Helena, Ascension, and Tristan da Cunha; South Georgia and South Sandwich Islands; Sovereign Base Areas on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia); and the Turks and Caicos Islands. (See [http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-us/what-we-do/overseas-territories].) ISO 3166-1 contains entries for twelve of the fourteen British Overseas Territories. The two British Overseas Territories omitted from ISO 3166-1 are the British Antarctic Territory (ISO includes no national Antarctic claims) and the Sovereign Base Area on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia, as a single B.O.T.). Note that ISO 3166-2 does not contain code elements for any of those territories as an administrative subdivision of the United Kingdom. GENC also contains specific top-level entries for the same twelve British Overseas Territories found in ISO 3166-1, and in addition, GENC contains separate entries for each of Akrotiri, Dhekelia, and Diego Garcia.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: ANTARCTICA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:usRecognitionNote: Antarctica consists of the territory south of 60 degrees south latitude. This area includes claims by ARGENTINA, AUSTRALIA, CHILE, FRANCE, NEW ZEALAND, NORWAY, and the UNITED KINGDOM, the legal status of which remains in suspense under the terms of the Antarctic Treaty of 1959. The UNITED STATES recognizes no claims to Antarctica.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: ANTIGUA AND BARBUDA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: In order to correct a naming anomaly, the GENC Standard specifies the remarks "Includes Redonda", while ISO 3166-1 specifies "Includes Redonda Island".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: ARUBA

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The GENC Standard specifically excludes the geospatial extent of Aruba from the entry named "NETHERLANDS". Note that, although ISO 3166-1 includes an entry named "ARUBA", ISO 3166-2 correspondingly specifies a code element for Aruba as an administrative subdivision (of type "country") of the entry named "NETHERLANDS" (see ISO 3166-1:2013, Clause 4.3 "Overlaps"; and ISO 3166-2:2013, Clause 4.1.2 (on subdivision)). In the GENC Standard, the territory of Aruba is represented exclusively by the entry named "ARUBA". Note: There may be ambiguity in the standards between the country of the Netherlands and the Kingdom of the Netherlands.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: ASHMORE AND CARTIER ISLANDS
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:fullName: Territory of Ashmore and Cartier Islands
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard includes these ISO user-assigned code elements for Baker Island. A numeric code element has additionally been assigned by the CCWG. ISO 3166-1 does not contain a separate entry for Baker Island.
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Note that ISO 3166-1 considers the entry named "AUSTRALIA" as including the geographic territory of the Ashmore and Cartier Islands.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: AUSTRALIA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Commonwealth of Australia" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Australia".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because GENC Standard considers the entry named "AUSTRALIA" to specifically exclude the geospatial extent of the Ashmore and Cartier Islands, Christmas Island, the Cocos (Keeling) Islands, the Coral Sea Islands, Heard Island and McDonald Islands, and Norfolk Island; each of those territories has a distinct entry in the GENC Standard. Note that ISO 3166/MA considers the entry named "AUSTRALIA" as specifically including the geographic territory of the Ashmore and Cartier Islands, and the Coral Sea Islands (see the ISO 3166-1 Remarks). Note that ISO 3166-2 does not include any external territories as administrative subdivisions under the entry named "AUSTRALIA". (See ISO 3166-1:2013, Clause 4.3 "Overlaps"; and ISO 3166-2:2013, Clause 4.1.2 (on subdivision).)

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: AZERBAIJAN

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: BAHAMAS, THE

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: BAKER ISLAND

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Note that ISO 3166-2 includes Baker Island as an administrative subdivision (of type "islands, groups of islands") of the ISO 3166-1 entry named "UNITED STATES MINOR OUTLYING ISLANDS". The two British Overseas Territories omitted from ISO 3166-1 are the British Antarctic Territory (ISO includes no national Antarctic claims) and the Sovereign Base Area on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia, as a single B.O.T.). genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: BHUTAN
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Kingdom of Bhutan" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Kingdom of Bhutan", and the GENC Standard does not include the local short name "Druk-Yul" in 'dz'/'dzo'.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: BOLIVIA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the name "BOLIVIA" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "BOLIVIA (PLURINATIONAL STATE OF)"; GENC specifies the short name "Bolivia" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Bolivia (Plurinational State of)"; and GENC specifies the full name "Plurinational State of Bolivia" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Plurinational State of Bolivia".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: BONAIRE, SINT EUSTATIUS, AND SABA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:usRecognitionNote: Special municipalities administered by the NETHERLANDS
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard differs from ISO 3166-1 in the punctuation of the name; the GENC Standard uses a comma before the "and" in all forms of the name, whereas ISO 3166-1 does not. In particular, the GENC Standard specifies the name "BONAIRE, SINT EUSTATIUS, AND SABA" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "BONAIRE, SINT EUSTATIUS AND SABA"; GENC specifies the short name "Bonaire, Sint Eustatius, and Saba" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Bonaire, Sint Eustatius and Saba"; and GENC specifies the full name "Bonaire, Sint Eustatius, and Saba" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Bonaire, Sint Eustatius and Saba". Additionally, the GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'en'/'eng' as "Bonaire, Sint Eustatius, and Saba" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Bonaire, Sint Eustatius and Saba", and the GENC Standard does not include local short names in either 'nl'/'nld' or '--'/'pap'.
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The GENC Standard specifically excludes the geospatial extent of Bonaire, Sint Eustatius, and Saba from the entry named "NETHERLANDS". Note that, although ISO 3166-1 includes a collective entry named "BONAIRE, SINT EUSTATIUS AND SABA", ISO 3166-2 specifies code elements for Bonaire, Sint Eustatius, and Saba individually as administrative subdivisions (of type "special municipalities") of both the entry "BONAIRE, SINT EUSTATIUS AND SABA", and of the entry named "NETHERLANDS" (see ISO 3166-1:2013, Clause 4.3 "Overlaps"; and ISO 3166-2:2013, Clause 4.1.2 (on subdivision)). In the GENC Standard, the territory of Bonaire, Sint Eustatius, and Saba is represented exclusively by the entry named "BONAIRE, SINT EUSTATIUS, AND SABA". Note: There appears to be an ambiguity in ISO 3166 between "NETHERLANDS" as representing the country of the Netherlands or the Kingdom of the Netherlands.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: BOTSWANA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Botswana" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Botswana".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: BOUVET ISLAND
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Bouvet Island is under Norwegian sovereignty, but it is not a part of the geospatial extent of Norway. The English-language site of Statistics Norway ([http://www.ssb.no/english/subjects/00/minifakta_en/en/]) gives the dimensions of Norway in coordinates, all of which are in the Northern Hemisphere; also, it lists the total area (in square kilometers) of the Kingdom of Norway as including the areas of Svalbard and Jan Mayen, with a separate listing for the Antarctic Territories (including Bouvet Island); the Antarctic area is not added into the total for the Kingdom of Norway. Note that both the top-level GENC and ISO 3166-1 contain entries for Bouvet Island. Also note that there is no administrative subdivision for Norway under the entry "NORWAY" in ISO 3166-2.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: BRAZIL
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Federative Republic of Brazil" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Federative Republic of Brazil". In order to correct multiple naming anomalies (and identify included areas with greater specificity) the GENC Standard specifies the remarks "Includes Atol das Rocas, Arquipélago de Fernando de Noronha, Ilha da Trindade, Ilhas Martin Vaz, and Penedos de São Pedro e São Paulo", while ISO 3166-1 specifies "Includes Fernando de Noronha Island, Martim Vaz Islands, Trindade Island". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'pt'/'por' as "Brasil", removing the definite article, where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Brasil (o)".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: BRITISH INDIAN OCEAN TERRITORY
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the short name "British Indian Ocean Territory" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "British Indian Ocean Territory (the)"; and GENC specifies the full name "British Indian Ocean Territory" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "British Indian Ocean Territory (the)". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'en'/'eng' as "British Indian Ocean Territory" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "British Indian Ocean Territory (the)".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because GENC Standard considers the entry named "BRITISH INDIAN OCEAN TERRITORY" to specifically exclude the geospatial extent of the atoll Diego Garcia; the GENC Standard includes a distinct top-level entry for "DIEGO GARCIA". ISO 3166/MA considers the entry named "BRITISH INDIAN OCEAN TERRITORY" to include Diego Garcia, as stated in ISO 3166-1. British Indian Ocean Territory is a British Overseas Territory. British Overseas Territories are distinct areas that are not part of the territory of the United Kingdom. There are 14 such territories, including: Anguilla; Bermuda; British Antarctic Territory; British Indian Ocean Territory; British Virgin Islands; Cayman Islands; Falkland Islands (Islas Malvinas); Gibraltar; Montserrat; Pitcairn Islands; Saint Helena, Ascension, and Tristan da Cunha; South Georgia and South Sandwich Islands; Sovereign Base Areas on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia); and the Turks and Caicos Islands. (See [http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-us/what-we-do/overseas-territories].) ISO 3166-1 contains entries for twelve of the fourteen British Overseas Territories. The two British Overseas Territories omitted from ISO 3166-1 are the British Antarctic Territory (ISO includes no national Antarctic claims) and the Sovereign Base Area on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia, as a single British Overseas Territory). Note that ISO 3166-2 does not contain code elements for any of those territories as an administrative subdivision of the United Kingdom. The GENC Standard also contains specific top-level entries for the same twelve British Overseas Territories found in ISO 3166-1, and in addition, the GENC Standard contains separate entries for each of Akrotiri, Dhekelia, and Diego Garcia.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: BRUNEI
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the name "BRUNEI" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "BRUNEI DARUSSALAM"; and GENC specifies the short name "Brunei" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Brunei Darussalam". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'en'/'eng' as "Brunei" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Brunei Darussalam".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The GENC Standard specifically excludes the geospatial extent of the Spratly Islands from the entry named "BRUNEI"; those islands in the South China Sea are claimed in their entirety by China (including Taiwan) and Vietnam, and in part by Brunei, Malaysia, and Philippines. The ISO 3166/MA may consider some or all of the territory of the Spratly Islands to be included under the ISO 3166-1 entry named "BRUNEI DARUSSALAM".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: BULGARIA

The two British Overseas Territories omitted from ISO 3166-1 are the British Antarctic Territory (ISO includes no national Antarctic claims) and the Sovereign Base Area on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia, as a single British Overseas Territory). Note that ISO 3166-2 does not contain code elements for any of those territories as an administrative subdivision of the United Kingdom. GENC also contains specific top-level entries for the same twelve British Overseas Territories found in ISO 3166-1, and in addition, GENC contains separate entries for each of Akrotiri, Dhekelia, and Diego Garcia.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the short name "Central African Republic" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Central African Republic (the)"; and GENC specifies the full name "Central African Republic" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Central African Republic". genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: CHAD

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: CHILE
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Chile" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Chile". In order to correct multiple naming anomalies the GENC Standard specifies the remarks "Includes Easter Island, Archipiélago Juan Fernández, Isla Sala y Gómez, Isla San Ambrosio, Isla San Félix", while ISO 3166-1 specifies "Includes Easter Island, Juan Fernández Islands, Sala y Gómez Island, San Ambrosio Island, San Félix Island".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: CHINA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "People’s Republic of China" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the People's Republic of China". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'zh'/'zho' as "Zhonghua Renmin Gongheguo" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Zhongguo". Note that ISO 3166-1 consistently uses the incorrect character U+0027 rather than U+2019.
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because GENC Standard considers the entry named "CHINA" as specifically excluding the geospatial extent of Hong Kong, Macau, and Taiwan, each of which has a distinct entry in the GENC Standard. The ISO 3166/MA considers their geography territory to be included under the ISO 3166-1 entry named "CHINA"; while ISO 3166-1 includes entries named "HONG KONG", "MACAO", and "TAIWAN, PROVINCE OF CHINA", they are also included in ISO 3166-2 as administrative subdivisions of China, with the names "Hong Kong" and "Macao" (both of type: special administrative region) and "Taiwan" (type: province). In the GENC Standard, those three territories are represented exclusively by the entries named "HONG KONG", "MACAU" and "TAIWAN". The GENC Standard also specifically excludes the geospatial extent of the Paracel Islands from coverage under the entry named "CHINA"; those islands in the South China Sea are claimed in their entirety by China (including Taiwan) and Vietnam. The GENC Standard represents them with a separate entry named "PARACEL ISLANDS". The GENC Standard also specifically excludes the Spratly Islands from coverage under the entry named "CHINA"; those islands in the South China Sea are claimed in their entirety by China (including Taiwan) and Vietnam, and in part by Brunei, Malaysia, and Philippines. The GENC Standard represents them with a separate entry named "SPRATLY ISLANDS". The ISO 3166/MA may consider some or all of the territory of the Paracel Islands or Spratly Islands to be included under the ISO 3166-1 entry named "CHINA" (for example, the standard is not detailed enough to tell whether the administrative subdivision named "Hainan" (code element: CN-46) includes the Paracel Islands).

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: CHRISTMAS ISLAND
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Territory of Christmas Island" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Christmas Island".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Both the GENC Standard and ISO 3166/MA consider the geospatial extent of Christmas Island as external to the territory of Australia. The GENC Standard contains separate top-level entries for the external territories of Australia (including the Ashmore and Cartier Islands, Christmas Island, the Cocos (Keeling) Islands, the Coral Sea Islands, Heard Island and McDonald Islands, and Norfolk Island); as a general principle, top-level GENC entries do not overlap in territory. The Australian external territories that have entries in ISO 3166-1 (Christmas Island, the Cocos (Keeling) Islands, Heard Island and McDonald Islands, and Norfolk Island) do not have corresponding entries as administrative subdivisions in ISO 3166-2, thus are not included in the geospatial extent of Australia (see ISO 3166-1:2013, Clause 4.3 "Overlaps"; and ISO 3166-2:2013, Clause 4.1.2 (on subdivision)).

The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'fr'/'fra' as "Congo" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Congo (la République démocratique du)". genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: CURAÇAO

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard does not include "Curaçao" as a local short name in 'en'/'eng'.
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The GENC Standard specifically excludes the geospatial extent of Curaçao from the entry named "NETHERLANDS". Note that, although ISO 3166-1 includes an entry named "CURAÇAO", ISO 3166-2 correspondingly specifies a code element for Curaçao as an administrative subdivision (of type "country") of the entry named "NETHERLANDS" (see ISO 3166-1:2013, Clause 4.3 "Overlaps"; and ISO 3166-2:2013, Clause 4.1.2 (on subdivision)). In the GENC Standard, the territory of Curaçao is represented exclusively by the entry named "CURAÇAO". genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: CYPRUS
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Cyprus" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Cyprus".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because GENC Standard considers the geopolitical entity named "CYPRUS" to specifically exclude the geospatial extent of both Akrotiri and Dhekelia, which are represented by distinct top-level entries in the GENC Standard. There is no entry for Akrotiri or Dhekelia in ISO 3166-1 or ISO 3166-2. It is not clear whether ISO 3166/MA considers the code elements for the entry named "UNITED KINGDOM" as covering the territories of Akrotiri and Dhekelia; however, neither Akrotiri nor Dhekelia appears in the ISO 3166-2 administrative subdivisions of the United Kingdom, so the presumption is that their territory is not included under that entry (see ISO 3166-2:2013, Clause 4.1.2 (on subdivision)). The two Sovereign Base Areas of Akrotiri and Dhekelia together constitute the British Overseas Territory on Cyprus that was ceded to the United Kingdom in the 1960 Treaty of Establishment, in which the U.K. granted independence to the Crown Colony of Cyprus; the U.K., Cyprus, and Turkey were all signatories to that treaty. Note that British Overseas Territories are not considered part of the territory of the United Kingdom (see [http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-us/what-we-do/overseas-territories].) Apart from the Sovereign Base Areas on Cyprus, all of the other British Overseas Territories have their own separate entries in ISO 3166-1 (and in the GENC Standard as well).

Note that British Overseas Territories are not considered part of the territory of the United Kingdom (see [http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-us/what-we-do/overseas-territories].) Apart from the Sovereign Base Areas on Cyprus, all of the other British Overseas Territories have their own separate entries in ISO 3166-1 (and in the GENC Standard as well).

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Fiji" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Fiji", and the GENC Standard does not include the local short name "Viti" in 'fj'/'fij'.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: FINLAND
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Finland" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Finland".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: FRANCE
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "French Republic" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the French Republic". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'fr'/'fra' as "France", removing the definite article, where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "France (la)".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because GENC Standard considers the geopolitical entity named "FRANCE" as excluding the geospatial extent of the dependency of Clipperton Island; the overseas departments of French Guiana, Guadeloupe, Martinique, Mayotte, and Reunion; the overseas territorial collectivities of French Polynesia, New Caledonia, Saint Barthelemy, Saint Martin, Saint Pierre and Miquelon, and Wallis and Futuna; and the overseas territory of the French Southern Lands, because each of those geographic territories is represented by a distinct entry in the GENC Standard. Note that ISO 3166-1 states that the entry named "FRANCE" includes all of those geographic territories, and ISO 3166-2 specifies code elements for them as administrative subdivisions of France.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: FRENCH GUIANA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Department of Guiana" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "French Guiana". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'fr'/'fra' as "Guyane", removing the definite article, where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Guyane (la)".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The GENC Standard specifically excludes the geospatial extent of French Guiana from the entry named "FRANCE". Note that ISO 3166-1 states that the entry named "FRANCE" includes French Guiana, and ISO 3166-2 specifies code elements for a corresponding administrative subdivision (of type "overseas department") named "Guyane (française)" (local name).

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: FRENCH POLYNESIA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifically excludes the geospatial extent of French Polynesia from the entry named "FRANCE". Additionally, in order to correct multiple naming anomalies the GENC Standard specifies the remarks "Comprises Îles Tubuaï, Îles Gambier, Îles Marquises, Society Islands (principal island: Tahiti), and Archipel des Tuamotu.", while ISO 3166-1 specifies "Comprises Austral Islands, Gambier Islands, Marquesas Islands, Society Archipelago (principal island: Tahiti), and the Tuamotu Islands." The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'fr'/'fra' as "Polynésie Française" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Polynésie française (la)".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Note that ISO 3166-1 states that the entry named "FRANCE" includes French Polynesia, and ISO 3166-2 specifies code elements for a corresponding administrative subdivision (of type "overseas territorial collectivity") named "Polynésie française" (local name).

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: FRENCH SOUTHERN AND ANTARCTIC LANDS
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the name "FRENCH SOUTHERN AND ANTARCTIC LANDS" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "FRENCH SOUTHERN TERRITORIES"; GENC specifies the short name "French Southern and Antarctic Lands" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "French Southern Territories (the)"; and GENC specifies the full name "French Southern and Antarctic Lands" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "French Southern Territories (the)". Additionally, in order to correct multiple naming anomalies the GENC Standard specifies the remarks "Comprises Île Amsterdam, Îles Crozet, Îles Kerguelen, and Île Saint-Paul", while ISO 3166-1 specifies "Comprises Amsterdam Island, Crozet Archipelago, Kerguelen Islands, Saint-Paul Island and and French scattered Indian Ocean Islands formed by Bassas da India, Europa Island, Glorioso Islands, Juan de Nova Island and Tromelin Island". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'fr'/'fra' as "Terres Australes et Antarctiques Françaises" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Terres australes françaises (les)".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because GENC Standard considers the geopolitical entity named "FRENCH SOUTHERN AND ANTARCTIC LANDS" as specifically excluding the geospatial extent of Bassas da India, Europa Island, Glorioso Islands, Juan de Nova Island, and Tromelin Island, because each of those territories has a distinct entry in the GENC Standard. Note that ISO 3166-1 states that the entry named "FRENCH SOUTHERN LANDS" includes all of those territories (and also that French Southern Lands is itself included in the entry named "FRANCE"). Both the GENC Standard and ISO 3166-1 exclude the geographic territory of the French-claimed portion of Antarctica (Terre Adelie), which instead is covered by the entry named "ANTARCTICA".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GABON
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Gabonese Republic" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Gabonese Republic". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'fr'/'fra' as "Gabon" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Gabon (le)".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GAMBIA, THE
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the name "GAMBIA, THE" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "GAMBIA"; GENC specifies the short name "Gambia, The" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Gambia (the)"; and GENC specifies the full name "Republic of The Gambia" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of The Gambia". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'en'/'eng' as "Gambia, The" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Gambia (The)".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GAZA STRIP

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The Gaza Strip is a geospatial component of the GENC entry named "PALESTINIAN TERRITORY".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GERMANY
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Federal Republic of Germany" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Federal Republic of Germany".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GHANA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Ghana" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Ghana".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GIBRALTAR
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Gibraltar is a British Overseas Territory. British Overseas Territories are distinct areas that are not part of the territory of the United Kingdom. There are 14 such territories, including: Anguilla; Bermuda; British Antarctic Territory; British Indian Ocean Territory; British Virgin Islands; Cayman Islands; Falkland Islands (Islas Malvinas); Gibraltar; Montserrat; Pitcairn Islands; Saint Helena, Ascension, and Tristan da Cunha; South Georgia and South Sandwich Islands; Sovereign Base Areas on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia); and the Turks and Caicos Islands. (See [http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-us/what-we-do/overseas-territories].) ISO 3166-1 contains entries for twelve of the fourteen British Overseas Territories. The two British Overseas Territories omitted from ISO 3166-1 are the British Antarctic Territory (ISO includes no national Antarctic claims) and the Sovereign Base Area on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia, as a single British Overseas Territory). Note that ISO 3166-2 does not contain code elements for any of those territories as an administrative subdivision of the United Kingdom. GENC also contains specific top-level entries for the same twelve British Overseas Territories found in ISO 3166-1, and in addition, GENC contains separate entries for each of Akrotiri, Dhekelia, and Diego Garcia.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GLORIOSO ISLANDS
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:usRecognitionNote: Administered by FRANCE, claimed by MADAGASCAR and COMOROS
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard includes these ISO user-assigned code elements for the Guantanamo Bay Naval Base. A numeric code element has additionally been assigned by the CCWG.

Note that ISO 3166-1 considers the Glorioso Islands to be included in the entry named "FRENCH SOUTHERN TERRITORIES".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GREECE
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Hellenic Republic" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Hellenic Republic".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GREENLAND

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard does not include the local short name "Grønland" in 'da'/'dan'.

Each has a separate entry in the GENC Standard, as well as in ISO 3166-1, and Greenland is not listed in ISO 3166-2 as an administrative subdivision of the entry named "DENMARK" (see ISO 3166-2:2013, Clause 4.1.2 (on subdivision)).

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GUADELOUPE

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GUAM
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Territory of Guam" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Guam".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because GENC Standard considers the geographic territory of Guam to be specifically excluded from the geographic territory of the entry named "UNITED STATES". Note that the ISO 3166/MA considers the United States as including the geographic territory of Guam; while ISO 3166-1 includes an entry named "GUAM", ISO 3166-2 specifies a code element for Guam as a corresponding administrative subdivision (of type "outlying area") of the entry named "UNITED STATES" (see ISO 3166-1:2013, Clause 4.3 "Overlaps"; and ISO 3166-2:2013, Clause 4.1.2 (on subdivision)).

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GUANTANAMO BAY NAVAL BASE
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:usRecognitionNote: U.S. Naval Base Area operated under a perpetual lease granting "complete jurisdiction and control" of the area although CUBA retains ultimate sovereignty.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Guantanamo Bay Naval Base is a U.S. Naval Base Area operated under a perpetual lease granting "complete jurisdiction and control" of the area although the Republic of Cuba retains ultimate sovereignty. There is no entry for Guantanamo Bay Naval Base in ISO 3166-1 or ISO 3166-2. It is not clear whether ISO 3166/MA would consider the geographic territory of Guantanamo Bay Naval Base to be covered by the code elements for the ISO 3166-1 entry named "CUBA".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GUATEMALA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Guatemala" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Guatemala".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GUERNSEY
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Bailiwick of Guernsey" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Guernsey", and the GENC Standard does not include the local short name "Guernesey" in 'fr'/'fra'.
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Guernsey is part of the Channel Islands, which is a British Crown Dependency, and therefore not included in the territory of the United Kingdom (see the web site of the British Monarcy regarding the Channel Islands: [http://www.royal.gov.uk/MonarchUK/QueenandCrowndependencies/ChannelIslands.aspx].) Both the GENC Standard and ISO 3166-1 represent Guernsey as a top-level entry. Also note that ISO 3166-2 does not contain code elements for Guernsey as an administrative subdivision of the entry named "UNITED KINGDOM".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GUINEA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Guinea" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Guinea". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'fr'/'fra' as "Guinée" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Guinée (la)".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GUINEA-BISSAU
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Guinea-Bissau" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Guinea-Bissau".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: GUYANA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Co-operative Republic of Guyana" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Guyana".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: HAITI
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Haiti" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Haiti".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: HEARD ISLAND AND MCDONALD ISLANDS
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:fullName: Territory of Heard Island and McDonald Islands
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Territory of Heard Island and McDonald Islands" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Heard Island and McDonald Islands".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Both the GENC Standard and ISO 3166/MA consider the geospatial extent of Heard Island and McDonald Islands as external to the territory of Australia. The GENC Standard contains separate top-level entries for the external territories of Australia (including the Ashmore and Cartier Islands, Christmas Island, the Cocos (Keeling) Islands, the Coral Sea Islands, Heard Island and McDonald Islands, and Norfolk Island); as a general principle, top-level GENC entries do not overlap in territory. The Australian external territories that have entries in ISO 3166-1 (Christmas Island, the Cocos (Keeling) Islands, Heard Island and McDonald Islands, and Norfolk Island) do not have corresponding entries as administrative subdivisions in ISO 3166-2, thus are not included in the geospatial extent of Australia (see ISO 3166-1:2013, Clause 4.3 "Overlaps"; and ISO 3166-2:2013, Clause 4.1.2 (on subdivision)).

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: HONDURAS
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Honduras" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Honduras".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: HONG KONG
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Hong Kong Special Administrative Region" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region of China".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because GENC Standard considers the geospatial extent of Hong Kong to be distinct from that covered by the entry named "CHINA"; it is represented exclusively by the GENC entry named "HONG KONG". Note that ISO 3166/MA considers the entry named "CHINA" as including the geographic territory of Hong Kong; ISO 3166-1 includes an entry named "HONG KONG", but also ISO 3166-2 specifies a corresponding administrative subdivision (of type "special administrative region") named "Hong Kong".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: HOWLAND ISLAND
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard includes these ISO user-assigned code elements for Jan Mayen (distinct from those for Svalbard). A numeric code element has additionally been assigned by the CCWG. ISO 3166-1 includes a single composite entry named "SVALBARD AND JAN MAYEN".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Note that ISO 3166-2 includes Howland Island as an administrative subdivision (of type "islands, groups of islands") of the ISO 3166-1 entry named "UNITED STATES MINOR OUTLYING ISLANDS". ISO 3166-2 includes a corresponding entry named "United States Minor Outlying Islands", which is an administrative subdivision (of type "outlying area") of the entry named "UNITED STATES". The ISO 3166-1 entry "UNITED STATES MINOR OUTLYING ISLANDS" comprises nine U.S. islands and island groups that are represented by separate entries at the top level of the GENC Standard.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: ICELAND
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Iceland" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Iceland".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: INDIA

(See the web site of the British Monarcy regarding the Channel Islands: [http://www.royal.gov.uk/MonarchUK/QueenandCrowndependencies/ChannelIslands.aspx]; also see [http://www.direct.gov.uk/en/governmentcitizensandrights/livingintheuk/dg_10012517].) genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: ISRAEL

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: JAN MAYEN

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: JERSEY

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: MONTSERRAT
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Montserrat is a British Overseas Territory. British Overseas Territories are distinct areas that are not part of the territory of the United Kingdom. There are 14 such territories, including: Anguilla; Bermuda; British Antarctic Territory; British Indian Ocean Territory; British Virgin Islands; Cayman Islands; Falkland Islands (Islas Malvinas); Gibraltar; Montserrat; Pitcairn Islands; Saint Helena, Ascension, and Tristan da Cunha; South Georgia and South Sandwich Islands; Sovereign Base Areas on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia); and the Turks and Caicos Islands. (See [http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-us/what-we-do/overseas-territories].) ISO 3166-1 contains entries for twelve of the fourteen British Overseas Territories. The two British Overseas Territories omitted from ISO 3166-1 are the British Antarctic Territory (ISO includes no national Antarctic claims) and the Sovereign Base Area on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia, as a single British Overseas Territory). Note that ISO 3166-2 does not contain code elements for any of those territories as an administrative subdivision of the United Kingdom. GENC also contains specific top-level entries for the same twelve British Overseas Territories found in ISO 3166-1, and in addition, GENC contains separate entries for each of Akrotiri, Dhekelia, and Diego Garcia.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Note that ISO 3166-2 includes Palmyra Atoll as an administrative subdivision (of type "islands, groups of islands") of the ISO 3166-1 entry named "UNITED STATES MINOR OUTLYING ISLANDS". The ISO 3166-1 entry "UNITED STATES MINOR OUTLYING ISLANDS" comprises nine U.S. islands and island groups that are represented by separate entries at the top level of the GENC Standard.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: PARACEL ISLANDS
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:usRecognitionNote: Occupied by CHINA, claimed by TAIWAN and VIETNAM
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard includes these ISO user-assigned code elements for the Paracel Islands. A numeric code element has additionally been assigned by the CCWG.

The Paracel Islands in the South China Sea are claimed in their entirety by China (including Taiwan) and Vietnam.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: PARAGUAY
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Paraguay" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Paraguay", and the GENC Standard does not include the local short name "Paraguay" in 'gn'/'grn'. The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'es'/'esp' as "Paraguay" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Paraguay (el)".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: PERU
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Peru" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Peru". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'es'/'esp' as "Perú" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Perú (el)", and the GENC Standard does not include local short names in either 'qu'/'que' or 'ay'/'aym'.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: PHILIPPINES
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the short name "Philippines" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Philippines (the)"; and GENC specifies the full name "Republic of the Philippines" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of the Philippines". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'en'/'eng' as "Philippines", removing the definite article, where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Philippines (the)".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The GENC Standard entry named "PHILIPPINES" specifically excludes the geospatial extent of the Spratly Islands, which is represented by a distinct GENC entry named "SPRATLY ISLANDS". The Spratly Islands in the South China Sea are claimed in their entirety by China (including Taiwan) and Vietnam, and in part by Brunei, Malaysia, and Philippines. The ISO 3166/MA may consider some or all of the territory of the Spratly Islands to be included under the ISO 3166-1 entry named "PHILIPPINES".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: PITCAIRN ISLANDS
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:fullName: Pitcairn, Henderson, Ducie, and Oeno Islands
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the name "PITCAIRN ISLANDS" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "PITCAIRN"; GENC specifies the short name "Pitcairn Islands" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Pitcairn"; and GENC specifies the full name "Pitcairn, Henderson, Ducie, and Oeno Islands" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Pitcairn". In order to correct multiple naming anomalies the GENC Standard specifies the remarks "Includes Henderson Island, Ducie Atoll, and Oeno Atoll.", while ISO 3166-1 specifies "Includes Ducie Island, Henderson Island, and Oeno Island." The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'en'/'eng' as "Pitcairn Islands" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Pitcairn".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Pitcairn Islands is a British Overseas Territory. British Overseas Territories are distinct areas that are not part of the territory of the United Kingdom. There are 14 such territories, including: Anguilla; Bermuda; British Antarctic Territory; British Indian Ocean Territory; British Virgin Islands; Cayman Islands; Falkland Islands (Islas Malvinas); Gibraltar; Montserrat; Pitcairn Islands; Saint Helena, Ascension, and Tristan da Cunha; South Georgia and South Sandwich Islands; Sovereign Base Areas on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia); and the Turks and Caicos Islands. (See [http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-us/what-we-do/overseas-territories].) ISO 3166-1 contains entries for twelve of the fourteen British Overseas Territories. The two British Overseas Territories omitted from ISO 3166-1 are the British Antarctic Territory (ISO includes no national Antarctic claims) and the Sovereign Base Area on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia, as a single British Overseas Territory). Note that ISO 3166-2 does not contain code elements for any of those territories as an administrative subdivision of the United Kingdom. GENC also contains specific top-level entries for the same twelve British Overseas Territories found in ISO 3166-1, and in addition, GENC contains separate entries for each of Akrotiri, Dhekelia, and Diego Garcia.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: REUNION

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: RUSSIA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the name "RUSSIA" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "RUSSIAN FEDERATION"; GENC specifies the short name "Russia" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Russian Federation (the)"; and GENC specifies the full name "Russian Federation" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Russian Federation". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'ru'/'rus' as "Rossiya" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Rossijskaja Federacija".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because GENC Standard considers the geopolitical entity named "RUSSIA" as excluding the geospatial extent of the Etorofu, Habomai, Kunashiri, and Shikotan Islands, which collectively have a separate GENC entry named "ETOROFU, HABOMAI, KUNASHIRI, AND SHIKOTAN ISLANDS". Note that ISO 3166-1 may consider the entry named "RUSSIAN FEDERATION" as including the geographic territory of the Etorofu, Habomai, Kunashiri, and Shikotan Islands (southernmost members of the Kuril Islands) as a component of the ISO 3166-2 Sakhalin Oblast administrative subdivision (which is of type "administrative region").

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: SAINT HELENA, ASCENSION, AND TRISTAN DA CUNHA

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:fullName: Saint Helena, Ascension, and Tristan da Cunha
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard differs ISO 3166-1 in the punctuation of the name; GENC uses a comma before the "and" in all forms of the name, whereas ISO 3166-1 does not. In particular, the GENC Standard specifies the name "SAINT HELENA, ASCENSION, AND TRISTAN DA CUNHA" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "SAINT HELENA, ASCENSION AND TRISTAN DA CUNHA"; GENC specifies the short name "Saint Helena, Ascension, and Tristan da Cunha" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha"; and GENC specifies the full name "Saint Helena, Ascension, and Tristan da Cunha" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha". In order to correct a naming anomaly the GENC Standard specifies the remarks "Comprises: Saint Helena Island, Ascension Island, Tristan da Cunha Group (Gough Island, Inaccessible Island, Nightingale Island and Stoltenhoff Island).", while ISO 3166-1 specifies "Comprises: Saint Helena Island, Ascension Island, Tristan da Cunha Archipelago (Gough Island, Inaccessible Island, Nightingale Island and Stoltenhoff Island)."
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Saint Helena, Ascension, and Tristan da Cunha (together) is a British Overseas Territory. British Overseas Territories are distinct areas that are not part of the territory of the United Kingdom. There are 14 such territories, including: Anguilla; Bermuda; British Antarctic Territory; British Indian Ocean Territory; British Virgin Islands; Cayman Islands; Falkland Islands (Islas Malvinas); Gibraltar; Montserrat; Pitcairn Islands; Saint Helena, Ascension, and Tristan da Cunha; South Georgia and South Sandwich Islands; Sovereign Base Areas on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia); and the Turks and Caicos Islands. (See [http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-us/what-we-do/overseas-territories].) ISO 3166-1 contains entries for twelve of the fourteen British Overseas Territories. The two British Overseas Territories omitted from ISO 3166-1 are the British Antarctic Territory (ISO includes no national Antarctic claims) and the Sovereign Base Area on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia, as a single British Overseas Territory). Note that ISO 3166-2 does not contain code elements for any of those territories as an administrative subdivision of the United Kingdom. GENC also contains specific top-level entries for the same twelve British Overseas Territories found in ISO 3166-1, and in addition, GENC contains separate entries for each of Akrotiri, Dhekelia, and Diego Garcia.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:usRecognitionNote: Claimed entirely or in part by CHINA, MALAYSIA, PHILIPPINES, TAIWAN, and VIETNAM
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard includes these ISO user-assigned code elements for the Spratly Islands. A numeric code element has additionally been assigned by the CCWG.
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The GENC Standard entry named "SPRATLY ISLANDS" uses user-assigned code elements to represent these disputed islands in the South China Sea, while ISO 3166-1 does not include a specific entry for them. These islands in the South China Sea are claimed in their entirety by China (including Taiwan) and Vietnam, and in part by Malaysia and Philippines. In addition, Brunei claims waters adjacent to the Spratly Islands based both on the extent of its continental shelf and on its exclusive economic zone (under the UN Convention on the Law of the Sea).

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: TAIWAN
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:usRecognitionNote: The United States has maintained unofficial relations with Taiwan since 1979, consistent with the U.S. one China policy, as reflected in the three U.S.-PRC Joint Communiqués and the Taiwan Relations Act (P.L. 96-8).
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the name "TAIWAN" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "TAIWAN, PROVINCE OF CHINA"; GENC specifies the short name "Taiwan" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Taiwan (Province of China)"; and GENC specifies the full name "Taiwan" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Taiwan (Province of China)". Additionally, in order to correct a naming anomaly the GENC Standard specifies the remarks "Includes the Pescadores (Penghu Qundao)", while ISO 3166-1 specifies "Includes the Penghu (Pescadores) Islands."
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because GENC Standard does not include Taiwan as a province under the entry named "CHINA". The GENC Standard considers the geospatial extent of Taiwan to be distinct from that covered by the entry named "CHINA", and to be represented exclusively by the GENC entry named "TAIWAN". Note that ISO 3166/MA considers the entry named "CHINA" as including the geographic territory of Taiwan; ISO 3166-1 includes an entry named "TAIWAN, PROVINCE OF CHINA", but also ISO 3166-2 specifies a corresponding administrative subdivision (of type "province") named "Taiwan". Additionally, the GENC Standard specifically excludes the geospatial extent of the Paracel Islands and of the Spratly Islands from the GENC entry named "TAIWAN". The Paracel Islands in the South China Sea are claimed by China (including Taiwan) and by Vietnam. The Spratly Islands in the South China Sea are claimed in their entirety by China (including Taiwan) and Vietnam, and in part by Brunei, Malaysia, and Philippines. The GENC Standard represents both with distinct entries ("PARACEL ISLANDS" and "SPRATLY ISLANDS"). The ISO 3166/MA may consider some territory of the Paracel Islands or Spratly Islands to be included under the ISO 3166-1 entry named "TAIWAN, PROVINCE OF CHINA".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: TAJIKISTAN

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: TANZANIA

The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'sw'/'swa' as "Tanzania" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Jamhuri ya Muungano wa Tanzania".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: THAILAND

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Democratic Republic of Timor-Leste" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Democratic Republic of Timor-Leste". The GENC Standard revises the local short name in '--'/'tet' to "Timor Lorosa’e" (in ISO 3166-1 an incorrect character is used: U+0027 rather than U+2019).

The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'fr'/'fra' as "Togo" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Togo (le)".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: TONGA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Kingdom of Tonga" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Kingdom of Tonga", and the GENC Standard does not include the local short name "Tonga" in 'to'/'ton'.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: TRINIDAD AND TOBAGO
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Trinidad and Tobago" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Trinidad and Tobago".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: TROMELIN ISLAND
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:usRecognitionNote: Administered by FRANCE, claimed by MAURITANIA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard includes these ISO user-assigned code elements for Tromelin Island. A numeric code element has additionally been assigned by the CCWG.
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because GENC Standard considers the GENC entry named "FRENCH SOUTHERN AND ANTARCTIC LANDS" as specifically excluding the geospatial extent of Tromelin Island (one of the French scattered Indian Ocean islands). Note that ISO 3166-1 considers Tromelin Island to be included in the entry named "FRENCH SOUTHERN TERRITORIES".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: TUNISIA

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: TURKEY
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Turkey" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Turkey".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: TURKS AND CAICOS ISLANDS
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the short name "Turks and Caicos Islands" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Turks and Caicos Islands (the)"; and GENC specifies the full name "Turks and Caicos Islands" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Turks and Caicos Islands (the)". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'en'/'eng' as "Turks and Caicos Islands" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Turks and Caicos Islands (the)". The GENC standard does not include the remark "Territory: Caicos Islands".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The Turks and Caicos Islands is a British Overseas Territory. British Overseas Territories are distinct areas that are not part of the territory of the United Kingdom. There are 14 such territories, including: Anguilla; Bermuda; British Antarctic Territory; British Indian Ocean Territory; British Virgin Islands; Cayman Islands; Falkland Islands (Islas Malvinas); Gibraltar; Montserrat; Pitcairn Islands; Saint Helena, Ascension, and Tristan da Cunha; South Georgia and South Sandwich Islands; Sovereign Base Areas on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia); and the Turks and Caicos Islands. (See [http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-us/what-we-do/overseas-territories].) ISO 3166-1 contains entries for twelve of the fourteen British Overseas Territories. The two British Overseas Territories omitted from ISO 3166-1 are the British Antarctic Territory (ISO includes no national Antarctic claims) and the Sovereign Base Area on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia, as a single British Overseas Territory). Note that ISO 3166-2 does not contain code elements for any of those territories as an administrative subdivision of the United Kingdom. GENC also contains specific top-level entries for the same twelve British Overseas Territories found in ISO 3166-1, and in addition, GENC contains separate entries for each of Akrotiri, Dhekelia, and Diego Garcia.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: TUVALU
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard does not include the local short name "Tuvalu" in '--'/'tvl'.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: UGANDA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Uganda" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Uganda".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: UKRAINE
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'uk'/'ukr' as "Ukrayina" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Ukraina".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: UNITED ARAB EMIRATES
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the short name "United Arab Emirates" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "United Arab Emirates (the)"; and GENC specifies the full name "United Arab Emirates" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the United Arab Emirates". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'ar'/'ara' as "Al Imārāt al ‘Arabīyah al Muttaḩidah" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Al Imārāt".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: UNITED KINGDOM
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:fullName: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the name "UNITED KINGDOM" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "UNITED KINGDOM OF GREAT BRITAIN AND NORTHERN IRELAND"; GENC specifies the short name "United Kingdom" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland (the)"; and GENC specifies the full name "United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'en'/'eng' as "United Kingdom" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland (the)".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Based on research into the British Overseas Territories (which include: Akrotiri and Dhekelia; Anguilla; Bermuda; British Antarctic Territory; British Indian Ocean Territories; Cayman Islands; Falkland Islands (Islas Malvinas); Gibraltar; Montserrat; Pitcairn Island; Saint Helena, Ascension, and Tristan da Cunha; South Georgia and South Sandwich Islands; Turks and Caicos Islands and the Virgin Islands, British), those territories are considered external to the territory of the United Kingdom. (See [http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-us/what-we-do/overseas-territories].) And ISO 3166-1 represents 12 of the 14 territories with specific entries; it does not include an entry for the British Antarctic Territory, or for the Sovereign Base Area of Akrotiri and Dhekelia. Thus either those U.K. Sovereign Base Areas are unrepresented in ISO 3166-1, or they are represented under the entry named "UNITED KINGDOM". Even if the Sovereign Base Areas were covered using the code elements for the U.K., it is not clear whether ISO 3166-1 would be making the assertion that their territory is part of the U.K. (esecially when the U.K. does not make that assertion).

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: UNITED STATES
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the name "UNITED STATES" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "UNITED STATES OF AMERICA"; GENC specifies the short name "United States" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "United States of America (the)"; and GENC specifies the full name "United States of America" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the United States of America". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'en'/'eng' as "United States" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "United States of America (the)".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because GENC Standard considers the entry named "UNITED STATES" as specifically excluding the geographic territory of American Samoa, Guam, the Northern Mariana Islands, Puerto Rico, and the U.S. Virgin Islands. Each of those territories has a distinct entry in the GENC Standard. Note that the ISO 3166/MA considers the entry named "UNITED STATES" as including all of those territories, because ISO 3166-2 specifies code elements for a corresponding administrative subdivision in each case. (See ISO 3166-1:2013, Clause 4.3 "Overlaps"; and ISO 3166-2:2013, Clause 4.1.2 (on subdivision).) The GENC Standard also considers the entry named "UNITED STATES" as specifically excluding the geographic territory of Baker Island, Howland Island, Jarvis Island, Johnson Atoll, Kingman Reef, the Midway Islands, Navassa Island, Palmyra Atoll, and Wake Island; each of those territories has a distinct entry in the GENC Standard. Note that ISO 3166-2 includes each of those geographic territories as an administrative subdivision (of type "islands, groups of islands") under the entry named "UNITED STATES MINOR OUTLYING ISLANDS", which in turn is also represented in ISO 3166-2 as a corresponding administrative subdivision (of type "outlying area") of the entry named "UNITED STATES".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: UZBEKISTAN
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because the GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Uzbekistan" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Uzbekistan".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: VANUATU

In order to correct multiple naming anomalies the GENC Standard specifies the remarks "Principal islands: Éfaté, Espirito Santo", while ISO 3166-1 specifies "Principal islands: Efate, Santo". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'fr'/'fra' as "Vanuatu", removing the definite article, where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Vanuatu (le)".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: VATICAN CITY
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the name "VATICAN CITY" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "HOLY SEE"; GENC specifies the short name "Vatican City" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Holy See (the)"; and GENC specifies the full name "State of the Vatican City" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies no full name. The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'it'/'ita' as "Città del Vaticano" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Santa Sede (la)".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: VENEZUELA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the name "VENEZUELA" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "VENEZUELA (BOLIVARIAN REPUBLIC OF)"; GENC specifies the short name "Venezuela" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Venezuela (Bolivarian Republic of)"; and GENC specifies the full name "Bolivarian Republic of Venezuela" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Bolivarian Republic of Venezuela". Additionally, in order to correct a naming anomaly the GENC Standard specifies the remarks "Includes Isla de Aves", while ISO 3166-1 specifies "Includes Bird Island."

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: VIETNAM
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the name "VIETNAM" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "VIET NAM" (different spelling); GENC specifies the short name "Vietnam" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Viet Nam"; and GENC specifies the full name "Socialist Republic of Vietnam" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Socialist Republic of Vietnam".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The GENC Standard specifically excludes the geospatial extent of the Paracel Islands and of the Spratly Islands from the GENC entry named "VIETNAM". The Paracel Islands in the South China Sea are claimed by China (including Taiwan) and by Vietnam. The Spratly Islands in the South China Sea are claimed in their entirety by China (including Taiwan) and Vietnam, and in part by Brunei, Malaysia, and Philippines.The GENC Standard represents both with distinct entries ("PARACEL ISLANDS" and "SPRATLY ISLANDS"). The ISO 3166/MA may consider some territory of the Paracel Islands or Spratly Islands to be included under the ISO 3166-1 entry named "VIET NAM".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: VIRGIN ISLANDS, BRITISH
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the short name "Virgin Islands, British" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Virgin Islands (British)"; and GENC specifies the full name "Virgin Islands, British" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "British Virgin Islands (the)".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The British Virgin Islands is a British Overseas Territory. British Overseas Territories are distinct areas that are not part of the territory of the United Kingdom. There are 14 such territories, including: Anguilla; Bermuda; British Antarctic Territory; British Indian Ocean Territory; British Virgin Islands; Cayman Islands; Falkland Islands (Islas Malvinas); Gibraltar; Montserrat; Pitcairn Islands; Saint Helena, Ascension, and Tristan da Cunha; South Georgia and South Sandwich Islands; Sovereign Base Areas on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia); and the Turks and Caicos Islands. (See [http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-us/what-we-do/overseas-territories].) ISO 3166-1 contains entries for twelve of the fourteen British Overseas Territories. The two British Overseas Territories omitted from ISO 3166-1 are the British Antarctic Territory (ISO includes no national Antarctic claims) and the Sovereign Base Area on Cyprus (Akrotiri and Dhekelia, as a single British Overseas Territory). Note that ISO 3166-2 does not contain code elements for any of those territories as an administrative subdivision of the United Kingdom. GENC also contains specific top-level entries for the same twelve British Overseas Territories found in ISO 3166-1, and in addition, GENC contains separate entries for each of Akrotiri, Dhekelia, and Diego Garcia.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: VIRGIN ISLANDS, U.S.
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the short name "Virgin Islands, U.S." where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Virgin Islands (U.S.)"; and GENC specifies the full name "United States Virgin Islands" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Virgin Islands of the United States". The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'en'/'eng' as "Virgin Islands of the United States", removing the definite article, where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Virgin Islands of the United States (the)".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The entry for this geopolitical entity is assigned the GENC status of 'Exception' because GENC Standard considers the geographic territory of the U.S. Virgin Islands to be specifically excluded from the geographic territory of the entry named "UNITED STATES". Note that the ISO 3166/MA considers the United States as including the geographic territory of the U.S. Virgin Islands; while ISO 3166-1 includes an entry named "VIRGIN ISLANDS, U.S.", ISO 3166-2 specifies a code element for "Virgin Islands, U.S." as a corresponding administrative subdivision (of type "outlying area") of the entry named "UNITED STATES" (see ISO 3166-1:2013, Clause 4.3 "Overlaps"; and ISO 3166-2:2013, Clause 4.1.2 (on subdivision)).

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: WAKE ISLAND
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard includes these ISO user-assigned code elements for Wake Island. A numeric code element has additionally been assigned by the CCWG. ISO 3166-1 does not contain a separate entry for Wake Island.
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: Note that ISO 3166-2 includes Wake Island as an administrative subdivision (of type "islands, groups of islands") of the ISO 3166-1 entry named "UNITED STATES MINOR OUTLYING ISLANDS". ISO 3166-2 includes a corresponding entry named "United States Minor Outlying Islands", which is an administrative subdivision (of type "outlying area") of the entry named "UNITED STATES". The ISO 3166-1 entry "UNITED STATES MINOR OUTLYING ISLANDS" comprises nine U.S. islands and island groups that are represented by separate entries at the top level of the GENC Standard.

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: WALLIS AND FUTUNA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: In order to correct multiple naming anomalies the GENC Standard specifies the remarks "Comprises the Îles de Horne (principal island: Futuna) and Wallis Islands (principal island: Île Uvea).", while ISO 3166-1 specifies "Comprises the Hoorn Islands (principal island: Futuna) and Wallis Islands (principal island: Uvea)." The GENC Standard specifies the local short name for 'fr'/'fra' as "Wallis et Futuna" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "Wallis-et-Futuna".
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The GENC Standard specifically excludes the geospatial extent of Wallis and Futuna from the entry named "FRANCE". Note that ISO 3166-1 states that the entry named "FRANCE" includes the geographic territory of Wallis and Futuna, and ISO 3166-2 includes code elements for a corresponding administrative subdivision (of type "overseas territorial collectivity") named "Wallis-et-Futuna" (local name).

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: WEST BANK
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:usRecognitionNote: Israeli occupied; the status of the West Bank is a final status issue to be resolved through negotiations.
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard includes these ISO user-assigned code elements for the West Bank. A numeric code element has additionally been assigned by the CCWG.
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnTerritory: The West Bank is currently Israeli-occupied with its current status subject to the Israeli-Palstinian Interim Agreement; its permanent status is to be determined through further negotiation. The West Bank is a geospatial component of the GENC geopolitical entity named "PALESTINIAN TERRITORY".

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: WESTERN SAHARA
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:usRecognitionNote: Western Sahara is a non-self-governing territory. Its status is to be determined by the people of the Western Sahara.
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard does not consider the name to be provisional but specifies that the sovereignity is yet to be determined. The GENC Standard also revises the local short name in 'ar'/'ara' to "Aş Şaḩrā’ al Gharbīyah" (in ISO 3166-1 an incorrect character is used: U+0027 rather than U+2019).

genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:name: YEMEN
genc:GeopoliticalEntityEntry.genc:entryNotesOnNaming: The GENC Standard specifies the full name "Republic of Yemen" where instead ISO 3166-1 specifies "the Republic of Yemen". In order to correct a naming anomaly the GENC Standard specifies the remarks "Includes Socotra", while ISO 3166-1 specifies "Includes Socotra Island".
